    "These methods explore various aspects such as model training and architectures, document identifiers, incremental learning, task-specific adaptation, and generative recommendations.",
    "Figure 4 presents an overview of the GR system and we'll provide an in-depth discussion of each associated challenge in the following sections.",
    "Model Training and StructureOne of the core components of GR is the model training and structure, aiming to enhance the model's ability to memorize documents in the corpus.",
    "Model Training.To effectively train generative models for indexing documents, the standard approach is to train the mapping from queries to relevant DocIDs, based on standard sequence-tosequence (seq2seq) training methods, as described in Equation ( 2).",
    "This method has been widely used in numerous GR research works, such as DSI [281], NCI [307], SEAL [13], etc."
